description: >
  This rule enforces mobile and desktop compatibility for UI components built with React (Vite) 
  and styled using Tailwind CSS. It ensures a mobile-first approach with responsive design principles 
  and best coding practices across the project.

match:
  - "**/*.tsx"
  - "**/*.jsx"
  - "tailwind.config.js"
  - "vite.config.js"

instructions: |
  1. Use Tailwind CSS utility classes to implement responsive, mobile-first designs.
  2. Apply responsive prefixes (e.g., sm:, md:, lg:, xl:) to adjust layouts across different screen sizes.
  3. Ensure that all React components are modular, reusable, and follow best practices.
  4. Validate that UI components render correctly on both mobile and desktop devices.
  5. Keep the Tailwind and Vite configuration files in sync with your design system and build process.
  6. Write clear code comments to explain responsive design choices and configurations.

references:
  - "@file tailwind.config.js"
  - "@file vite.config.js"


